==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[homographic]] [[w:Grammatical case|case]] endings of the [[nominative]], [[accusative]], and [[vocative]] forms of numerous [[Appendix:Latin second declension#Neuter|neuter]] {{L.}} [[Appendix:Latin second declension#Neuter|second declension]] nouns.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|[[w:Latin spelling and pronunciation|Latin]]}}<sup>1</sup> {{IPA|/—um/}}
* {{a|Latin}}<sup>2</sup> {{IPA|/—ũ/}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/—əm/}}

===Suffix===
'''-um''' (''plural'' '''[[-a#English|-a]]''')

# ''Denotes [[singular]] [[grammatical]] [[number]].''

====Usage notes====
* The vast majority of words which feature this suffix also have standard ''-ums'' plurals formed by suffixation with the {{term|-s|lang=en}} plural suffix. However, in such situations, the {{term||-s}} suffix morphologically is additional to and separate from the {{term||-um}} suffix.

